Press Releases.Title: 34 New Cases of Covid-19 Infection
Press Releases.MainContent:
1. As of 5 September 2020, 12pm, the Ministry of Health (MOH) has preliminarily confirmed an additional 34 cases of COVID-19 infection in Singapore. Based on our investigations so far, there are 3 cases in the community, of whom 1 is a Singaporean and 2 are Work Pass holders.

2. There are 2 imported cases, both of whom had been placed on Stay-Home Notice upon arrival in Singapore.

3. We are still working through the details of the cases, and further updates will be shared via the MOH press release that will be issued tonight.


MINISTRY OF HEALTH
5 SEPTEMBER 2020
